reviews.text:
such a deliciously complex and chocolatey profile... the INW milk chocolate predominates, beefed up by the gingerbread without seeming "spicy" or dry (in fact quite velvety). notes of cinnamon, almond, and marshmallow round out the edges. the touch of lemon sicily is a master stroke! somehow it binds to the sugary sweetness of the meringue and keeps the otherwise dense profile from feeling too heavy, all without taking it anywhere confusing.&#xD;
&#xD;
this was my first trial of CAP SS and the batch came out too sweet for me at .8%, but that's not to take away from the recipe otherwise. excellent job, thanks so much!
